@page "/about"

<div class="about-page">
    <div class="about-container">

        <!-- Consistent Page Hero -->
        <section class="page-hero fade-in delay-0">
            <p class="page-eyebrow">About</p>

            <h1>Background and Approach</h1>

            <p class="page-intro">
                A more personal look at how I think, what I build, and the approach behind my work.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Personal Intro -->
        <section class="about-section about-intro fade-in delay-1">
            <div class="about-intro-grid">
                <div class="about-intro-copy">
                    <div class="section-heading">
                        <p class="section-label about-label">Introduction</p>
                        <h2>Building things that are meant to work.</h2>
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        What stands out most about development is the process of taking an idea,
                        shaping it into something real, and refining it until it feels intentional.
                        That includes the structure underneath, the way it looks, and the way it works for the person using it.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        The best projects feel like a balance between design and function —
                        clean enough to navigate, practical enough to be useful, and solid enough to keep improving over time.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="about-intro-image-wrap">
                    <img src="images/your-photo.jpg" alt="Portrait of David Padilla" class="about-intro-image" />
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Development Approach -->
        <section class="about-section about-build fade-in delay-2">
            <div class="section-heading">
                <p class="section-label">Development Approach</p>
                <h2>How I Build</h2>
            </div>

            <ul class="about-build-list">
                <li>Real applications over isolated demos</li>
                <li>UI designed for structure, clarity, and usability</li>
                <li>Frontends connected to APIs, services, and persistent data</li>
                <li>Clean, maintainable code with component-based architecture</li>
                <li>Projects tested and deployed in live Azure environments</li>
                <li>Iteration guided by real usage, not just first implementation</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Background -->
        <section class="about-section about-background fade-in delay-3">
            <div class="background-grid">
                <div class="background-copy">
                    <div class="section-heading">
                        <p class="section-label background-label">Background</p>
                        <h2>What Shaped My Approach</h2>
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        A background in IT, operations, and Army service shaped the way problems get approached:
                        stay calm, look at the system, and figure out what actually needs to work.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        That mindset carried naturally into software development. Building applications from the ground up
                        became a way to combine technical structure, usability, and the kind of problem-solving that feels both practical and creative.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="background-image-wrap">
                    <img src="images/your-second-photo.jpg" alt="David Padilla outdoors" class="background-image" />
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

    </div>
</div>